üìò Security Concepts ‚Äì PG-DITISS (Aug 2025)
Session 24: Web-Based, Network-Based & Social Engineering Attacks on Android
üîπ BASIC MCQs (10)
1. Web-based attacks on Android devices mainly target:
A. Hardware components
B. Mobile browsers and web apps
C. Battery performance
D. Screen resolution

2. Network-based attacks usually exploit:
A. UI flaws
B. Network communication weaknesses
C. File permissions
D. App icons

3. Social engineering attacks primarily manipulate:
A. Network protocols
B. Operating systems
C. Human behavior
D. Encryption algorithms

4. MITM attack stands for:
A. Mobile Internet Threat Model
B. Man-In-The-Middle
C. Mobile Intrusion Technique
D. Multi-Interface Traffic Method

5. Packet sniffing involves:
A. Encrypting packets
B. Capturing network traffic
C. Blocking network access
D. Modifying apps

6. Phishing attacks mainly aim to:
A. Increase availability
B. Steal sensitive information
C. Improve performance
D. Patch systems

7. Android devices are vulnerable to MITM when using:
A. Encrypted VPN
B. Secure HTTPS
C. Open or unsecured Wi-Fi
D. Mobile data

8. Web-based attacks often exploit:
A. Browser vulnerabilities
B. Hardware drivers
C. BIOS
D. Power supply

9. Packet sniffing threatens which CIA principle the MOST?
A. Availability
B. Integrity
C. Confidentiality
D. Authentication

10. Social engineering attacks are dangerous because they:
A. Use malware only
B. Bypass technical security controls
C. Require hacking skills
D. Are slow

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE MCQs (10)
11. MITM attacks allow attackers to:
A. Shut down servers
B. Intercept and modify communication
C. Encrypt traffic
D. Patch applications

12. Which Android network scenario is MOST risky?
A. HTTPS over VPN
B. Open public Wi-Fi
C. Encrypted WPA3 Wi-Fi
D. Mobile data

13. Packet sniffing on Android is easier when traffic is:
A. Encrypted
B. Compressed
C. Plaintext
D. Signed

14. Phishing attacks commonly use:
A. Exploits
B. Fake websites or messages
C. Rootkits
D. Port scans

15. MITM attacks on mobile often use:
A. ARP poisoning
B. SQL Injection
C. MAC flooding only
D. Buffer overflow

16. Which tool is commonly used for packet sniffing in labs?
A. Nmap
B. Metasploit
C. Wireshark
D. Nessus

17. Network-based attacks mainly target which OSI layer?
A. Physical
B. Network / Transport
C. Presentation
D. Application only

18. Social engineering attacks include:
A. Smishing and phishing
B. Port scanning
C. MAC spoofing
D. SQL Injection

19. Phishing attacks on mobile devices often succeed because:
A. Large screens
B. Users trust messages on phones
C. Strong encryption
D. Secure OS

20. Packet sniffing during MITM attacks helps attackers to:
A. Increase speed
B. Capture credentials and data
C. Patch traffic
D. Improve routing

üî∫ ADVANCED MCQs (10) ‚Äì CCEE TRAP + LAB-FOCUSED
21. Which combination BEST describes a MITM attack?
A. DoS + Flooding
B. Interception + Manipulation
C. Encryption + Authentication
D. Scanning + Reporting

22. HTTPS reduces MITM impact because it:
A. Blocks packets
B. Encrypts communication
C. Improves speed
D. Uses UDP

23. Why phishing is more effective on mobile devices?
A. Weak OS
B. Smaller screens hide URL details
C. No encryption
D. Rooted devices

24. Network-based attacks on Android MOST commonly violate:
A. Availability
B. Confidentiality
C. Performance
D. Scalability

25. MITM attacks are easier when users ignore:
A. Battery warnings
B. Certificate warnings
C. App updates
D. Screen brightness

26. Packet sniffing combined with ARP poisoning results in:
A. DoS
B. MITM
C. MAC flooding
D. DNS scanning

27. Phishing differs from malware attacks because phishing:
A. Exploits software bugs
B. Relies on user deception
C. Requires root access
D. Uses kernel exploits

28. Best countermeasure against MITM on mobile is:
A. Open Wi-Fi
B. HTTPS + VPN
C. MAC spoofing
D. Plain HTTP

29. Social engineering attacks violate which security principle MOST?
A. Availability
B. Confidentiality
C. Authentication
D. Performance

30. Session 24 mainly tests understanding of:
A. Mobile UI design
B. Network + human-based mobile attacks
C. Hardware troubleshooting
D. Database security

